    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>As the message says, you have to go to Apple, not Sun, for Java on the Mac. As far as I know, Apple JDK 6 is installed by default on Mac OS X 10.6 (Snow Leopard). Maybe you need to install the developer tools from your Mac OS X installation DVD (the dev tools are an optional install from the OS DVD).</p>\n\n<p>See: <a href=\"http://developer.apple.com/java/\" rel=\"noreferrer\">http://developer.apple.com/java/</a></p>\n\n<p><strong>NOTE</strong> This answer from 16 Oct 2009 is now outdated; you can get the JDK for Mac OS X from the regular <a href=\"http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/index.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">JDK download page</a> on Oracle's website now.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 49198,
      "reputation" : 5669,
      "user_id" : 146408,
      "user_type" : "registered",
