    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>As a rule you cannot install other versions of Java on a Mac than those provided by Apple through Software Update.  If you need Java 6 you must have a 64-bit Intel computer.  You should always have Java 5 and 1.4 and perhaps 1.3 installed if you have at least OS X 10.4.</p>\n\n<p>If you have VERY much elbow grease and is willing to work with beta software you can install the OpenJDK under OS X, but I don't think you want to go there.</p>\n"
  }, {
