    "creation_date" : 1255694687,
    "answer_id" : 1577663,
    "question_id" : 1577014,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p><strong>The explanation is that JDK is a bit specific and does not contain the library tools.jar</strong>. For my development, I need this library and Mac's JDK doesn't provide it:</p>\n\n<p>(Cf. <a href=\"http://developer.apple.com/mac/library/documentation/Java/Conceptual/Java14Development/02-JavaDevTools/JavaDevTools.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">http://developer.apple.com/mac/library/documentation/Java/Conceptual/Java14Development/02-JavaDevTools/JavaDevTools.html</a>)</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>tools.jar does not exist. Classes usually located here are instead included in classes.jar. Scripts that rely on the existence of tools.jar need to be rewritten accordingly.</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>It sucks!</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 64422,
      "reputation" : 1185,
      "user_id" : 190189,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/0fd04dbadaefe8b88e3e1bb3aac5949d?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
