    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I bought a MacBook Pro yesterday (<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OS_X_Mountain_Lion\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Mac&nbsp;OS&nbsp;X&nbsp;v10.8</a> (Mountain Lion)) and there is no JDK installed by default...</p>\n\n<p>As well as javac, I also found it didn't have packages such as <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apache_Subversion\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">SVN</a> installed. It turns out you can get everything from the <a href=\"https://developer.apple.com/downloads/index.action\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Apple developer page</a> (you will need to register with your AppleID). SVN is part of the \"Command Line Tools\" package.</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/9LhiY.png\" alt=\"Enter image description here\"></p>\n\n<p>This is what happens on a fresh MacBook:</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/gO7De.png\" alt=\"Enter image description here\"></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/hm33e.png\" alt=\"Enter image description here\"></p>\n\n<p>Hopefully this will help out other newbies like me ;)</p>\n"
