    "answer_id" : 34455392,
    "question_id" : 1577014,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you installed brew, cmd below will be helpful:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>brew cask install java</p>\n</blockquote>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 6052716,
      "reputation" : 1962,
      "user_id" : 4859182,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 92,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/9b05b4929050705b8fd73afc0e0c6eb5?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "solomkinmv",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4859182/solomkinmv"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1490349007,
    "creation_date" : 1490349007,
    "answer_id" : 42996179,
    "question_id" : 1577014,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>The easiest way is to use <a href=\"https://brew.sh/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Homebrew</a>. \nInstall Homebrew and then:</p>\n\n<pre><code>brew tap caskroom/versions\nbrew cask install java7\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>You can list all available versions using the following command:\n<code>brew cask search java</code></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 11029928,
      "reputation" : 3320,
      "user_id" : 8101556,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 80,
      "profile_image" : "https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-FXnR6vMV3yQ/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAFPA/CZXdhiJ7MFo/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
      "display_name" : "Rishikesh Darandale",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/8101556/rishikesh-darandale"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 2,
    "last_activity_date" : 1499429164,
    "creation_date" : 1499429164,
    "answer_id" : 44970360,
    "question_id" : 1577014,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Check this awesome tool <a href=\"http://sdkman.io/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">sdkman</a> to manage your jdk and other jdk related tools with great ease!</p>\n\n<p>e.g.</p>\n\n<pre><code>$sdk list java\n$sdk install java &lt;VERSION&gt;\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 322981,
        "reputation" : 346727,
        "user_id" : 642706,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 58,
        "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/ZWEI3.jpg?s=256",
        "display_name" : "Basil Bourque",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/642706/basil-bourque"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 1,
      "creation_date" : 1545239349,
      "post_id" : 53847892,
      "comment_id" : 94559941,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "I suggest you point out downloading from <a href=\"https://adoptopenjdk.net/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">AdoptOpenJDK.net</a>, and then follow your instructions, thereby avoiding the legal &amp; support issues of Oracle’s releases."
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 406004,
      "reputation" : 968,
      "user_id" : 775243,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/b34cbdca9cd3e0c9230065ca411c5a6a?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "LCC",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/775243/lcc"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 2,
    "last_activity_date" : 1570657275,
    "last_edit_date" : 1570657275,
    "creation_date" : 1545210744,
    "answer_id" : 53847892,
    "question_id" : 1577014,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Since most answers are out of date, here's what works as of end of 2018 under the assumption that</p>\n\n<ol>\n<li>You want to install the GPL version of OpenJDK.[0]</li>\n<li>You do not want to install Homebrew</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>In that case, grab the desired version from one the many available, freely usable OpenJDK editions, e.g.:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://adoptopenjdk.net/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">AdoptOpenJDK</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/corretto/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Amazon Corretto</a> (Great for production, includes <a href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/corretto/latest/corretto-11-ug/patches.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">backports</a>)</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://jdk.java.net/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Oracle GPLv2 OpenJDK</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Some of these include installers, but if not you can do the following.  Assuming here version 11.0.1 for Mac. In your favorite shell, run:</p>\n\n<pre><code>tar -xzf openjdk-11.0.1_osx-x64_bin.tar.gz\nsudo mv jdk-11.0.1.jdk /Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines\n# Fix owner and group\nsudo chown -R root:wheel /Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/jdk-11.0.1.jdk\n# (Optional) Check if the new JDK can be found\n/usr/libexec/java_home\n=&gt; /Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/jdk-11.0.1.jdk/Contents/Home\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>[0] Note that the Oracle branded JDK has <a href=\"https://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/terms/license/javase-license.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">significant licensing restrictions</a> allowing you its use basically <strong>only for testing, i.e., not for production.</strong> If you do not have a support agreement with Oracle, then it seems risky to me to use their JDK, especially since the <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/38685948\">differences to OpenJDK are minimal</a>.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Edit:</strong> added more choices</p>\n"
  }, {
